# initial_program.py

import random

# EVOLVE-BLOCK-START
def run_search():
    n = 47
    # all grid points
    grid = [(x,y) for x in range(n) for y in range(n)]
    S = []
    random.shuffle(grid)
    for (x,y) in grid:
        # check collinearity against every pair already in S
        is_collinear = False
        for i in range(len(S)):
            x1, y1 = S[i]
            for j in range(i + 1, len(S)):
                x2, y2 = S[j]
                # Calculate cross product once
                cross_product = (x2 - x1) * (y - y1) - (y2 - y1) * (x - x1)
                if cross_product == 0:
                    is_collinear = True
                    break
            if is_collinear:
                break
        if not is_collinear:
            S.append((x,y))
    print(len(S))
    return S
# EVOLVE-BLOCK-END
